Definition: feminine of {{h5081}}; properly, nobility, i.e. reputation; soul.
probably from an unused root meaning to give; a present (for prostitution); gift.

a primitive root; to push off; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.); banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.
from {{h5068}}; properly, voluntary, i.e. generous; hence, magnanimous; as noun, a grandee (sometimes a tyrant); free, liberal (things), noble, prince, willing (hearted).
a primitive root; to shove asunder, i.e. disperse; drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.
a primitive root; to promise (pos., to do or give something to God); (make a) vow.
of uncertain derivation; a sheath (of a sword); sheath.
(Aramaic) from the same as {{h5084}}; a sheath; figuratively, the body (as the receptacle of the soul); body.
or נֵדֶר; from {{h5087}}; a promise (to God); also (concretely) a thing promised; vow(-ed).
from an unused root meaning to lament; lamentation; wailing.
a primitive root; to groan; groan.
from {{h5008}}; a groan; groaning.
from {{h5001}}; an oracle; (hath) said, saith.
a primitive root; to commit adultery; figuratively, to apostatize; adulterer(-ess), commit(-ing) adultery, woman that breaketh wedlock.
a primitive root; properly, to whisper, i.e. (by implication) to utter as an oracle; say.
a primitive root; to scorn; or (in Ecclesiastes 12:5), by interchange for {{h5132}}, to bloom; abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, × great, provoke.
or נֶאָצָה; from {{h5006}}; scorn; blasphemy.
from {{h5003}}; adultery; adultery.
from {{h5003}}; adultery; adultery.
the same as {{h5036}}; dolt; Nabal, an Israelite; Nabal.
from {{h5034}}; stupid; wicked (especially impious); fool(-ish, -ish man, -ish woman), vile person.

or נֵבֶל; from {{h5034}}; a skin-bag for liquids (from collapsing when empty); hence, a vase (as similar in shape when full); also a lyre (as having a body of like form); bottle, pitcher, psaltery, vessel, viol.

a primitive root; to wilt; generally, to fall away, fail, faint; figuratively, to be foolish or (morally) wicked; causatively, to despise, disgrace; disgrace, dishounour, lightly esteem, fade (away, -ing), fall (down, -ling, off), do foolishly, come to nought, × surely, make vile, wither.
from an unused root meaning to burst forth; a fountain; spring.
or נְבָיֹת; feminine plural from {{h5107}}; fruitfulnesses; Nebajoth, a son of Ismael, and the country settled by him; Nebaioth, Nebajoth.
feminine of {{h5030}}; a prophetess or (generally) inspired woman; by implication, a poetess; by association a prophet's wife; prophetess.
from {{h5012}}; a prophet or (generally) inspired man; prophecy, that prophesy, prophet.
feminine of {{h5036}}; foolishness, i.e. (morally) wickedness; concretely, a crime; by extension, punishment; folly, vile, villany.

from {{h5034}}; a flabby thing, i.e. a carcase or carrion (human or bestial, often collectively); figuratively, an idol; (dead) body, (dead) carcase, dead of itself, which died, (beast) that (which) dieth of itself.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5019}}; Nebuchadnezzar.
of foreign derivation; Nebushazban, Nebuchadnezzar's chief eunuch; Nebushazban.
feminine plural from the same as {{h5011}}; fruits; Naboth, an Israelite; Naboth.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a largess; reward.
a primitive root; to bark (as a dog); bark.
from {{h5024}}; a bark; Nobach, the name of an Israelite, and of a place East of the Jordan; Nobah.
of foreign origin; Nibchaz, a deity of the Avites; Nibhaz.
a primitive root; to scan, i.e. look intently at; by implication, to regard with pleasure, favor or care; (cause to) behold, consider, look (down), regard, have respect, see.
from {{h5027}}; regard; Nebat, the father of Jeroboam I; Nebat.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5030}}; a prophet; prophet.
feminine of {{h5099}}; snarling; disquietness, roaring.
a primitive root; to butt with the horns; figuratively, to war against; gore, push (down, -ing).
feminine of {{h5051}}; splendor; brightness.

or נָגִד; from {{h5046}}; a commander (as occupying the front), civil, military or religious; generally (abstractly, plural), honorable themes; captain, chief, excellent thing, (chief) governor, leader, noble, prince, (chief) ruler.
from {{h5055}}; butting, i.e. vicious; used (wont) to push.
from {{h5050}}; brilliancy (literally or figuratively); bright(-ness), light, (clear) shining.
a primitive root; to glitter; causatively, to illuminate; (en-) lighten, (cause to) shine.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5051}}; dawn; morning.
the same as {{h5051}}; Nogah, a son of David; Nogah.

a primitive root; properly, to thrum, i.e. beat a tune with the fingers; expectation. to play on a stringed instrument; hence (generally), to make music; player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, play(-er, -ing).

or נְגִינַת; (Psalm 61:title), from {{h5059}}; properly, instrumental music; by implication, a stringed instrument; by extension, a poem set to music; specifically, an epigram; stringed instrument, musick, Neginoth (plural), song.

a primitive root; properly, to front, i.e. stand boldly out opposite; by implication (causatively), to manifest; figuratively, to announce (always by word of mouth to one present); specifically, to expose, predict, explain, praise; bewray, × certainly, certify, declare(-ing), denounce, expound, × fully, messenger, plainly, profess, rehearse, report, shew (forth), speak, × surely, tell, utter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5046}}; to flow (through the idea of clearing the way); issue.
of uncertain derivation; Nibshan, a place in Palestine; Nibshan.

from an unused root meaning to be parched; the south (from its drought); specifically, the Negeb or southern district of Judah, occasionally, Egypt (as south to Palestine); south (country, side, -ward).
a primitive root; to gush forth; figuratively, to utter (good or bad words); specifically, to emit (a foul odor); belch out, flowing, pour out, send forth, utter (abundantly).
(Aramaic) from an unused root meaning to shine; a light; plural (collectively) a chandelier; candlestick.
from {{h5036}}; properly, disgrace, i.e. the (female) pudenda; lewdness.
apparently from {{h5036}} and {{h3909}}; foolish secrecy; Neballat, a place in Palestine; Neballat.

from {{h5046}}; a front, i.e. part opposite; specifically a counterpart, or mate; usually (adverbial, especially with preposition) over against or before; about, (over) against, × aloof, × far (off), × from, over, presence, × other side, sight, × to view.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5048}}; opposite; toward.
(Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick; a layer (of building materials); row.
from {{h5068}} and {{h3050}}; largess of Jah; Nedabjah, an Israelite; Nedabiah.

from {{h5068}}; properly (abstractly) spontaneity, or (adjectively) spontaneous; also (concretely) a spontaneous or (by inference, in plural) abundant gift; free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering).
from {{h5068}}; liberal; Nadab, the name of four Israelites; Nadab.
or נָדָא; (2 Kings 17:21), a primitive root; properly, to toss; figuratively, to exclude, i.e. banish, postpone, prohibit; cast out, drive, put far away.
passive participle of {{h5074}}; properly, tossed; abstractly, a rolling (on the bed); tossing to and fro.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5074}}; to depart; go from.

a primitive root; properly, to wave to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to rove, flee, or (causatively) to drive away; chase (away), × could not, depart, flee (× apace, away), (re-) move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).

from {{h5074}}; properly, rejection; by implication, impurity, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest); × far, filthiness, × flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, × removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness).
from {{h5077}} in the sense of freely flinging money; a bounty (for prostitution); gifts.
a primitive root; to impel; hence, to volunteer (as a soldier), to present spontaneously; offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5068}}; be (or give) liberal(-ly); (be minded of...own) freewill (offering), offer freely (willingly).
a primitive root; to flow; figuratively, to stretch out; causatively, to pour out or down; figuratively, to deliver over; fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.
a primitive root; to drive (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to tax, harass, tyrannize; distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), × raiser of taxes, taskmaster.

a primitive root; to be or come (causatively, bring) near (for any purpose); euphemistically, to lie with a woman; as an enemy, to attack; religious to worship; causatively, to present; figuratively, to adduce an argument; by reversal, to stand back; (make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.
from {{h5110}} in the sense of piling up; a mound, i.e. wave; heap.

a primitive root; properly, to touch, i.e. lay the hand upon (for any purpose; euphemistically, to lie with a woman); by implication, to reach (figuratively, to arrive, acquire); violently, to strike (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.); beat, (× be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.
from {{h5060}}; a blow (figuratively, infliction); also (by implication) a spot (concretely, a leprous person or dress); plague, sore, stricken, stripe, stroke, wound.
a primitive root; to push, gore, defeat, stub (the toe), inflict (a disease); beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, × surely, put to the worse.
from {{h5062}}; a trip (of the foot); figuratively, an infliction (of disease); plague, stumbling.
a primitive root; to groan, i.e. bewail; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to assemble (as if on proclamation); lament, wail.

a primitive root; to drive forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. lead, carry away; reflexively, to proceed (i.e. impel or guide oneself); also (from the panting induced by effort), to sigh; acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).
feminine of {{h5092}}; lamentation; doleful.
from {{h5091}}; an elegy; lamentation, wailing.
a primitive root; properly, to run with a sparkle, i.e. flow; hence (transitively), to conduct, and (by inference) to protect, sustain; carry, feed, guide, lead (gently, on).
(Aramaic) or נְהִירוּ; (Aramaic), from the same as {{h5105}}; illumination, i.e. (figuratively) wisdom; light.
from {{h5095}}; pasture; bush.
or נַהֲלֹל; the same as {{h5097}}; Nahalal or Nahalol, a place in Palestine; Nahalal, Nahallal, Nahalol.
from {{h5098}}; a snarl; roaring.
a primitive root; to growl; mourn, roar(-ing).

or נְבֻּכַדְנֶאצַּר; (2 Kings 24:1,10), or נְבוּכַדְנֶצַּר; (Esther 2:6; Daniel 1:18), or נְבוּכַדְרֶאצַּר; or נְבוּכַדְרֶאצּוֹר; (Ezra 2:1; Jeremiah 49:28), or foreign derivation; Nebukadnetstsar (or -retstsar, or -retstsor), king of Babylon; Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar.
of foreign origin; Nebuzaradan, a Babylonian general; Nebuzaradan.
the same as {{h5108}}; fruit; Nob, a place in Palestine; Nob.
a primitive root; to reject; abhor, make void.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5012}}; prophesy.
a primitive root; to prophesy, i.e. speak (or sing) by inspiration (in prediction or simple discourse); prophesy(-ing), make self a prophet.
probably of foreign derivation; Nebo, the name of a Babylonian deity, also of a mountain in Moab, and of a place in Palestine; Nebo.
a primitive root; to pierce; to be hollow, or (figuratively) foolish; hollow, vain.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5016}}; inspired teaching; prophesying.
from {{h5012}}; a prediction (spoken or written); prophecy.
